Offended, she never worked in film again.

title: In a Lonely Place - trailer - 09.png
caption: Screenshot from trailer for the movie In a Lonely Place (1950), featuring stars Gloria Grahame and Humphrey Bogart. The moment from the trailer that doesn't appear in the final cut. As Laurel (Gloria Grahame) is talking on the phone to the detective at the end of the film, Dix (Humphrey Bogart) starts to leave. In the "lost moment," Laurel calls out Dix's name and they have one last embrace on the steps before he leaves.

title: Winnipeg (6408553545).jpg
caption: Pantages Theatre, 180 Market Avenue - The Pantages Theatre opened in Winnipeg on Feb 9 1914. Its colourful American builder was Alexander Pantages a Seattle based impresario who wanted to build a string of new vaudeville houses for his touring acts. Pantages' Vaudeville circuit was a top quality chain of theatres and travelling acts that played in the western US and Canada. Alexander Pantages emigrated to the US as a boy from Greece. At age 13 he ended up in San Francisco and worked as an usher
